{{Infobox video game |title = Atlantis Underwater Tycoon |image = Atlantis Underwater Tycoon Coverart.jpg |developer = [[Activision Value]] |publisher = Activision Value |producer = Alex Jamieson, Zvonimir Miksic, Tim Whitehurst<ref name="mobygames"/> |designer = Joseph Cho<ref name="mobygames"/> |artist = |engine = |released = March 21, 2003<ref name="worthplaying"/><ref name="gamewatcher_review_new"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gamespot.com/atlantis-underwater-tycoon/ |title=Atlantis Underwater Tycoon |accessdate=2018-08-17 |work=[[GameSpot]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/games/atlantis-underwater-tycoon |title=Atlantis Underwater Tycoon PC |accessdate=2018-08-17 |work=[[IGN]]}}</ref><!-- Not sure if this is accurate: January 3, 2003<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.giantbomb.com/atlantis-underwater-tycoon/3030-6247/ |title=Atlantis Underwater Tycoon |accessdate=2018-08-18 |work=[[Giant Bomb]]}}</ref><ref name="gamewatcher_review_archived"/>--> |genre = [[City-building game|City-building]], [[Construction and management simulation|construction and management]], [[Business simulation game|business simulation]] |modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]] |platforms = [[Microsoft Windows]] }}
'''''Atlantis Underwater Tycoon''''' is an [[Ocean|underwater]] [[City-building game|city-building simulation game]] in which the player acts as a [[tycoon]] to simulate the [[Real-time game|real-time]] design and management of an [[Ocean colonization|underwater civilization]]. It was developed and published by [[Activision Value]], and released on March 21, 2003 for [[Microsoft Windows]] on the PC.
''Atlantis Underwater Tycoon'' was the first building sim to be set underwater.<ref name="worthplaying"/>
==Gameplay== In ''Atlantis Underwater Tycoon'', the player can choose to play in missions or in a sandbox-environment map to start building their underwater colony. The player chooses a tycoon character to play as who comes with their own positive and negative traits, such as providing bonus starting money, or having a disreputable attitude towards [[sea life]].
The player starts on the [[ocean floor]] with a home base and a set amount of money. The player then expands the [[Ocean colonization|underwater colony]] by constructing various residential, utility, commercial, industrial, tourist, and military buildings that extend outward from the home base in a design conducive to the ocean floor, linking them with air tubes, and [[terraforming]] the seabed if needed.<ref name="gamewatcher_review_archived"/><ref name="mobygames"/> The player is able to collect and store items produced by commercial and industrial buildings in warehouses and sell them off in a market. The player can also breed new wildlife to live in the city's waters, such as [[dolphin]]s or [[shark]]s, as well as create [[Submarine|underwater vehicles]] to roam around the city.<ref name="gamewatcher_review_archived"/> As the city grows, a wider range of buildings and residents become available. Such buildings include [[Blue whale|whale]] sanctuaries, [[sea turtle]] aquariums, shopping malls, [[Deepwater drilling|oil drills]], and prison facilities.<ref>{{cite web |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070109232346/http://pc.ign.com/objects/613/613977.html |url=http://pc.ign.com/objects/613/613977.html |archive-date=2007-01-09 |title=IGN: Atlantis Underwater Tycoon |work=[[IGN]] |accessdate=2018-08-18}}</ref> New and better buildings bring in more citizens and tourists, generating more income for the city. Over time, buildings nearing their life expectancies can be demolished to make room for new buildings.<ref name="mobygames">{{cite web |url=https://www.mobygames.com/game/atlantis-underwater-tycoon |title=Atlantis Underwater Tycoon (Windows) |work=[[MobyGames]] |accessdate=2018-08-17}}</ref> In the late stages of the game, the player can unlock the ability to build Atlantean structures.<ref name="gamewatcher_review_archived"/>
In addition to having to manage the economic aspects of the game, the player must also contend with attacks from enemy [[pirates]] and from enemy Atlanteans, as well as deal with underwater [[natural disaster]]s. Military vessels and friendly Atlantean defenders can be recruited to defend against such attacks.<ref name="gamewatcher_review_new">{{cite web |url=https://www.gamewatcher.com/reviews/atlantis-underwater-tycoon-review/10393 |title=Atlantis Underwater Tycoon Review |date=October 28, 2003 |accessdate=2018-08-18 |author=Chris |work=Gamewatcher}}</ref> Military buildings, such as [[Sonic weapon|sonic cannons]] and [[missile turret]]s, can be manned by the player to shoot projectiles at hostile vessels and destructive debris to destroy them.<ref name="gamewatcher_review_new"/>
On the whole, the player prevents the city from falling into harm by keeping a watchful eye out for enemy invaders and natural disasters, while managing the city's businesses so that population happiness, tourism, and sea life can prosper, all the while avoiding the city plunging into financial trouble.
==Reception== {{video game reviews | title = | subtitle = <!--Formatting--> | state = collapsible<!--plain/collapsible--> | align = right<!--left/right/none/inherit--> <!-- Aggregators --> | GR = | MC = <!-- Reviewers --> | XGP = | XPlay = | IGN = | GSpot = <!-- Custom aggregators limit is set to 10 --> | agg1 = | agg1Score = | agg2 = | agg2Score = <!-- Custom Reviewers limit is set to 10--> | rev1 = GameWatcher | rev1Score = 7.5/10<ref name="gamewatcher_review_archived">{{cite web |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110606054751/https://www.strategyinformer.com/pc/atlantisunderwatertycoon/review.html |archive-date=2011-06-06 |url=https://www.strategyinformer.com/pc/atlantisunderwatertycoon/review.html |accessdate=2011-06-06 |title=We play Atlantis Underwater Tycoon (PC)}}</ref><ref name="gamewatcher_score">{{cite web |url=https://www.gamewatcher.com/games/atlantis-underwater-tycoon |title=Atlantis Underwater Tycoon Summary |accessdate=2018-08-17 |work=GameWatcher}}</ref> | rev2 = PC Games (Germany) | rev2Score = 57%<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamechronicles.com/reviews/pc/axis/allies.htm |title=Unter dem Meer |work=PC Games (Germany) |date=October 18, 2003 |accessdate=2018-08-17}}</ref> | rev3 = JeuxVideoPC.com | rev3Score = 9/20<ref name="mobygames"/> | rev4 = GameStar (Germany) | rev4Score = 46/100<ref name="mobyrank">{{cite web |url=https://www.mobygames.com/game/windows/atlantis-underwater-tycoon/mobyrank |title=Atlantis Underwater Tycoon Reviews (Windows) |work=[[MobyGames]] |accessdate=2018-08-17}}</ref> | rev5 = Worthplaying.com | rev5Score = 7.8/10<ref name="worthplaying">{{cite web |url=https://worthplaying.com/article/2003/6/15/reviews/10653/ |title=PC Review - 'Atlantis: Underwater Tycoon' |author=Tristan |date=June 15, 2003 |accessdate=2018-08-18}}</ref> <!-- Awards No limit --> | award1Pub = | award1 = | award2Pub = | award2 = }}
''Atlantis Underwater Tycoon'' has been praised for its well-done visuals and its snappy underwater music track.<ref name="gamewatcher_review_new"/><ref name="gamewatcher_review_archived"/><ref name="worthplaying"/> The ability to see into buildings and view the people within nightclubs and movie theaters is also a nice plus.<ref name="worthplaying"/> The visual depiction of night and day from the rays of light shining down on the city also provides for a nice ambiance effect.<ref name="worthplaying"/> The top moments in the game can be attributed to the times when a player's prospering city "[comes] under attack from enemy subs, and the player reacts to mount a counter-attack to avoid all the player's hard work from being obliterated."<ref name="gamewatcher_review_archived"/>
One reviewer says that the game's biggest weakness lay in its lack of variety in building models and resources.<ref name="worthplaying"/>
