'''Hamidreza Taraghi''' ({{lang-fa|حمیدرضا ترقی}}) is an Iranian ''[[bazaari]]'' merchant<ref>{{Citation|author=Masoud Kazemzadeh|title= Intra-Elite Factionalism and the 2004 Majles Elections in Iran|journal=Middle Eastern Studies|year=2008|volume=44|number=2|doi=10.1080/00263200701874867|page=189–214|via=Taylor and Francis Online {{subscription}}|url=http://www.tandfonline.com/loi/fmes20}}</ref> and [[Iranian Principlists|conservative]] politician who served a member of the [[Parliament of Iran]] from 1996 to 2000 [[Mashhad and Kalat (electoral district)|Mashhad and Kalat electoral district]].<ref name="majlis"/>

Taraghi formerly headed [[Islamic Coalition Party]]'s bureau for international affairs.<ref>{{cite|url=http://theiranproject.com/blog/2014/11/08/iran-to-host-islamic-countries-parties-summit/|title=Iran to host Islamic countries parties’ summit|work=[[Mehr News Agency]]|date=8 November 2015|access-date=4 April 2017|via=The Iran Project}}</ref>
