{{Multiple issues| {{cleanup|date=January 2010}} {{BLP IMDb refimprove|date=January 2010}} }} [[File:Gassenhuber lugner.jpg|thumb|Richard Lugner (l.) with German painter Johann Gassenhuber]] [[File:Richard Lugner ROMY2008.jpg|thumb|Richard Lugner (Vienna 2008)]] '''Richard "Mörtel" Lugner'''<ref name="SD2014-09-13" /> (born 11 October 1932) is an [[Austria]]n entrepreneur in the [[construction industry]], a [[Vienna|Viennese]] society figure, and a former political candidate not affiliated with any of the Austrian political parties.{{Citation needed|date=January 2010}}
==Business career== Born in [[Vienna]], Lugner got a licence to work as a building contractor (''Baumeisterkonzession'') in 1962 and at first specialized in the erection of [[filling station]]s and the renovation of old buildings. His company started to prosper, and he eventually became known to a wider public with the completion, in 1979, of Vienna's first [[mosque]], situated on the banks of the river [[Danube]].
In 1990 he opened his own [[shopping mall]], ''Lugner City'', in a [[working class]] district of Vienna and, from the start, aggressively advertised his business by regularly inviting [[celebrity|celebrities]]&mdash;starting with [[Thomas Gottschalk]]&mdash;who would perform there and sign [[autograph]]s&mdash;a [[marketing]] strategy not very common in a city that, back then, hardly had any shopping malls.{{Citation needed|date=February 2010}} Through his shopping mall, Lugner was one of a small group of businesspeople who helped change Austrians' shopping habits by pushing to the limits the various regulations concerning [[shopping hours|opening hours]]. In a city where shops generally closed at 6 p.m. Mondays to Fridays and at noon on Saturdays to remain closed for more than one and a half days until Monday morning, Lugner strongly advocated late night shopping on at least one weekday and an extension of shopping hours to Saturday afternoon, even when that meant raising the [[trades union]]s' opposition.
==Celebrities== [[File:Nielsen Lugner 20120115.jpg|thumb|"Mörtel" Lugner with [[Brigitte Nielsen]] (c.) and his wife Christina, 2012 at his ''Lugner City'' mall]] In 1992 Mörtel and Mausi Lugner brought Harry Belafonte to Lugner City, and also took him along to the [[Vienna Opera Ball]]. From that time on, the couple have each year paid a celebrity to visit the shopping centre and then accompany them as their guest to that prestigious function at the Vienna State Opera, an "invitation" which has often been criticised or just belittled for being a nouveau riche idea. However, media attention has continually been rising, also abroad, so that today any official guests of honour are usually neglected compared to the Lugners' celebrities, who invariably have a status image: {{div col|colwidth=25em}} *1991 [[Gina Lollobrigida]] *1992 [[Harry Belafonte]] *1993 [[Joan Collins]] *1994 [[Ivana Trump]] *1995 [[Sophia Loren]] *1996 [[Grace Jones]] *1997 [[Sarah, Duchess of York]] *1998 [[Raquel Welch]] *1999 [[Faye Dunaway]] *2000 [[Jacqueline Bisset]] *2001 [[Farrah Fawcett]] *2002 [[Claudia Cardinale]] *2003 [[Pamela Anderson]] *2004 [[Andie MacDowell]] *2005 [[Geri Halliwell]] *2006 [[Carmen Electra]] *2007 [[Paris Hilton]] *2008 [[Dita von Teese]] *2009 [[Nicollette Sheridan]] *2010 [[Dieter Bohlen]] (originally meant to be [[Lindsay Lohan]] <ref name="lezgetreal">{{cite web |url=http://lezgetreal.com/?p=26387 |title=Lindsay Lohan Flakes on Opera Date |publisher=lezgetreal.com |author=Natasia Langfelder |accessdate=February 2, 2010 }}</ref> ) *2011 [[Larry Hagman]], [[Karima El Mahroug]] aka Ruby the Heart Stealer, and [[Zachi Noy]] *2012 [[Brigitte Nielsen]], [[Roger Moore]] *2013 [[Mira Sorvino]], [[Gina Lollobrigida]] *2014 [[Kim Kardashian]] *2015 [[Elisabetta Canalis]] *2016 [[Brooke Shields]] *2017 [[Goldie Hawn]] *2018 [[Melanie Griffith]] {{div col end}}
==Political ambitions==
In the late 1990s Richard Lugner handed over his business to his two grown-up sons by an earlier marriage, [[Alexander Lugner|Alexander]] and [[Andreas Lugner]], and went into [[politics]]. In the [[Austrian presidential election, 1998|1998 presidential elections]] he finished fourth in a field of five candidates, receiving 9.91 per cent of the popular vote; incumbent [[President of Austria|Federal President]] [[Thomas Klestil]], who had been running for a second term of office, received 63.4%. For the [[Austrian legislative election, 1999|parliamentary elections that took place the following year]], the Lugners organised a separate platform called ''Die Unabhängigen'' ("[[The Independents (Austria)|The Independents]]") but, as they only received 1.02 per cent of the vote, did not get any seats in the ''Nationalrat''. Nevertheless, at the end of the millennium, a survey found that more than 90 per cent of Austrians recognized the name ''Lugner''. For the [[Austrian presidential election, 2016|2016 presidential election]] he announced to collect the necessary signatures in order to participate.<ref>[http://www.marxist.com/political-earthquake-in-austria.htm ''Political Earthquake in Austria''] indicates received 2.4% in lowest turnout on record</ref>
==Personal== In September 2014, Lugner (aged 81) married [[Germany|German]] [[Playboy]] model [[Cathy Schmitz]] (aged 24) at a ceremony held at the [[Schönbrunn Palace]] in Vienna. Schmitz was a [[Playboy Bunny]] at the [[Playboy Club]] in [[Cologne]] before being the cover model of German Playboy in 2013. Lugner had been married four times before.<ref name="SD2014-09-13">[http://www.sueddeutsche.de/panorama/richard-moertel-lugner-hauptsache-die-leute-schauen-1.2127218 Hauptsache, die Leute schauen], Carolin Gasteiger, Suddeutsche, 13 September 2014, accessed 16 September 2014</ref><ref>[http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/playboy-model-cathy-schmitz-aged-24-marries-81-year-old-billionaire-richard-lugner-1465571 Playboy Model Cathy Schmitz, Aged 24, Marries 81-Year-Old Billionaire Richard Lugner], Toyin Owoseje, [[International Business Times]] 15 September 2014</ref>
Lugner has four children: His two sons, [[Alexander Lugner|Alexander]] and [[Andreas Lugner]], are from his first marriage. He has another child Nadine from a marriage to actress Sonja Jeannine. His youngest child, daughter Jacqueline (aged 21 in 2014), is from his 4th marriage.<ref name="SD2014-09-13" />
==Trivia== *''Die Lugners'' ("The Lugners") was a [[reality television|reality TV]] show produced by a private television broadcaster which showed Richard and Christina Lugner, their daughter, Jacqueline (born 1993), and Richard Lugner's mother-in-law, Martha Haidinger, at home, at work, and on holiday. *Christina Lugner has co-written a book, ''Fit für die Society. Wie Frauen sich erfolgreich machen'' ("Fit for Society. How Women Make Themselves Successful", 2004) ({{ISBN|3-7015-0473-3}}), in which she advises career women on questions of [[etiquette]].
