{{Infobox person | honorific_prefix = | name = Samia Zaman | honorific_suffix = | image = Samia Zaman (cropped).jpg | image_upright = | image_size = | alt = | caption = Zaman in Dhaka Lit Fest 2017 | native_name = সামিয়া জামান | native_name_lang = bn | pronunciation = | birth_date = <!-- {{birth date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | birth_place = [[Dhaka]], Bangladesh | nationality = Bangladeshi | alma_mater = [[University of Dhaka]] | occupation = Film director, television presenter | employer = | organization = [[Ekattor TV]] | agent = <!-- Discouraged in most cases, specifically when promotional, and requiring a reliable source --> | known_for = Journalist and film director | notable_works = | style = | home_town = | salary = | net_worth = <!-- Net worth should be supported with a citation from a reliable source --> | height = <!-- "X cm", "X m" or "X ft Y in" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) --> | weight = <!-- "X kg", "X lb" or "X st Y lb" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) --> | television = | title = <!-- Formal/awarded/job title. The parameter |office= may be used as an alternative when the label is better rendered as "Office" (e.g. public office or appointments) --> | spouse = | partner = <!-- (unmarried long-term partner) --> | children = | parents = | relatives = | family = | awards = [[Anannya Top Ten Awards]] (2008) | website = | signature = | footnotes = }}
'''Samia Zaman''' is a Bangladeshi media personality, filmmaker.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/magazine/2006/06/02/interview.htm|title=Reviving an Old Ritual|date=January 9, 2006|accessdate=2016-01-20|newspaper=The Daily Star|author=Aasha Mehreen Amin}}</ref> She was a television news presenter, reporter and talk show host. In 2006, she emerged as a film director. She also serves as the Editor and CEO of the television channel [[Ekattor TV]].<ref name=cannes>{{cite news|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/showbiz/cover-story/samia-zaman-bangladesh-cannes-102910|title=Samia Zaman: Bangladesh in Cannes|date=June 27, 2015|accessdate=2016-01-20|newspaper=The Daily Star|author=Rafi Hossain & M H Haider}}</ref>
==Career== In 1989, Zaman started out her career as a producer at the [[BBC World Service]] in London.<ref name=make>{{cite news|url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/magazine/2006/03/02/cover.htm|title="Make your own decisions"--Samia Zaman|date=March 10, 2006|accessdate=2016-01-20|newspaper=The Daily Star}}</ref> Zaman served as a journalist and news presenter in [[Ekushey Television]].<ref name=cannes/>
===Films=== In 1987 Zaman worked in the film ''Suchona'', with the director [[Morshedul Islam]] as an assistant.<ref name=make/> In 2006, she emerged as a filmmaker through her direction on the film ''[[Rani Kuthir Baki Itihash]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/2005/06/18/d506181402101.htm|date= June 18, 2005|title=Rani Kuthir Baki Itihash: Samia Zaman on her debut film|author=Novera Deepita|accessdate=2016-01-20|newspaper=The Daily Star}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/newDesign/news-details.php?nid=173657|title=Samia Zaman Calls the Shots|date=February 11, 2011|accessdate=2016-01-20|newspaper=The Daily Star}}</ref> She directed her second film, ''[[Aakash Koto Dure]]'', in 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/akash-koto-dure-14208|title=AKASH KOTO DURE|author=Mohammad Zahidul Islam|date=March 1, 2014|accessdate=2016-01-20|newspaper=The Daily Star}}</ref><ref name=cannes/>
In March 2015, Zaman served in the judge panel of Geneva International Oriental Film Festival.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/showbiz/grapevine/samia-geneva-73915|title=Samia in Geneva|date=March 28, 2015|accessdate=2016-01-20|newspaper=The Daily Star}}</ref>
==Personal life== Zaman has three daughters.<ref name=make/>
